    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Thanks @Buttaa and @djrtwo, I figured out what the issue was. To get the participation, we do the following steps:\r\n1. retrieve the state that's `requested_epoch + 1`, this requires replay historical blocks starting from an archived state.\r\n2. run `process_epoch` on the retrieved state  \r\n3. parse participations stats of previous epoch from the result of `process_epoch`\r\n\r\nThe mistake is in the loading of historical blocks for replay. We did not check whether the block is finalized. For participation at 1408, the node will request state at `start_slot(1049)` which is 45088. As we can see below, that block was orphaned. What made it worse was the orphaned block's parent slot is 45059, 29 slots behind. Because of that, the node's state only accounted for 45 attestations vs 1000+ attestations.\r\n\r\nhttps://beaconcha.in/block/45088\r\n\r\nAfter my fix:\r\n```\r\n{\"epoch\":\"1408\",\"finalized\":true,\"participation\":{\"globalParticipationRate\":0.75147694,\"votedEther\":\"614624000000000\",\"eligibleEther\":\"817888000000000\"}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThanks again for reporting this, I'm really glad we caught this one before mainnet!",
